    "To obtain the training data, a decomposition algorithm was used to separate resonant peaks from background spectrum for simulated data, and a CNN was applied as a classifier which can efficiently recognize the bands that resonances belong to (see Figure 4(g)).",
    "Due to this regularization of the model using physical knowledge, a much smaller amount of data was needed to obtain a very accurate model.",
    "And with the help of its reliable and rapid predicting capabilities, it was employed to design a bound state in the continuum (BIC) with infinite Q factor with an interior point algorithm.Together with the Q factor, the modal volume V is always considered for resonances at the same time [77].",
